{
  "texts": [
    "The fact that these variables are associated with adherence to rehabilitation programs necessitates the incorporation of these variables into studies that examine the effectiveness of AI-driven platforms for rehabilitation delivery 2.",
    "More importantly, home-based-and virtual-specific information or barriers to adherence to and completion of VRehab programs need to be collected and reported.",
    "These potential barriers include sensor and smart device installation and maintenance costs, internet connection stability 70, minimum system requirements of computers and smartphones for VRehab applications, type of residence (e.g., house, townhouse, apartment, community housing, or basement), digital literacy or computer skills of patients 57, and hearing or vision impairments.",
    "Among the reviewed home-based VRehab studies, only Qui et al.",
    "57 reported some of the barriers noted above, including residence type and computer skills."
  ]
}